==English==

===Etymology===
# (''noun'') contraction of '''[[omnibus]]'''. From Latin: '''[[omnibus]]''', meaning ''"for everything"'' or ''"for all"'', dative plural of ''"omnis"'', meaning ''"all"''.
# In electrical systems some sources name bus as a short form of ''"[[bus bar]]"''. Other sources name [[BUS]] as an abbreviation of [[Binar Units System]].

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /{{Unicode|ˈbɐs}}/
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: /bVs/

===Alternative spellings===
*'''[[buss]]''' ([[busses]]) - (for definition 2)

==={{abbreviation}}===
'''bus'''

# [[business]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# A [[motor]] [[vehicle]] for [[transport]]ing large numbers of [[people]] along [[road]]s.
# In an electric power distribution system, a large, usually inflexible, conductor to which other conductors are attached.
# In electrical systems: a connection between more than two attached devices.

